-- New Zealand Beats South Africa 38-27 to Win Rugby Championship
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-05T17:10:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-05/new-zealand-beats-south-africa-38-27-to-win-rugby-championship.html
Top-ranked New Zealand beat South
Africa 38-27 in their Rugby Championship decider to secure back-to-back titles.  Liam Messam touched down twice as New Zealand outscored
South Africa five tries to four at Ellis Park in Johannesburg.
Brian Habana scored two tries for the second-ranked Springboks.  New Zealand finished the southern hemisphere championship
with 28 points, nine more than second-place South Africa. Last-place Argentina hosts  Australia  later today in the competitionâ€™s
